# ============================================================
# .gitignore for the QSD workspace (public-repo-safe profile)
#
# This file is designed with publishing to a PUBLIC GitHub repo
# in mind. The rule of thumb: if a file is internal development
# breadcrumb, local operator tooling, or belongs to a different
# project, it stays out of git — even though it still lives on
# the operator's disk for their own use.
#
# Categories:
#   1. Secrets & credentials — catastrophic if leaked
#   2. Internal dev documents — fix memos, status notes, planning
#   3. Local operator scripts (Windows PowerShell helpers)
#   4. Projects unrelated to QSD
#   5. Build artifacts & runtime state
#   6. Language / IDE / OS caches
# ============================================================


# ------------------------------------------------------------
# 1) Secrets & credentials
# ------------------------------------------------------------
# VPS IP + root password. Primary SSH is ed25519; this file is a
# break-glass fallback for the DO web console.
vps.txt

# Scratch commit-message buffer used for HEREDOC-free git commits
# on Windows/PowerShell shells. The actual commit body lives in
# git history; the buffer is throwaway. The patterns cover the
# three conventions in active use across the project's tooling:
#   _commit_msg.txt          underscore-prefix (legacy)
#   _tmp_commit_msg.txt      underscore-prefix tmp variant
#   .commit_msg*             dot-prefix family (e.g. ops automation
#                            uses .commit_msg_docs.txt for scoped
#                            commit drafts; observed leaking to
#                            git status on 2026-05-18)
#   .git_commit_msg.tmp      dot-prefix .tmp variant (assistant's)
#   *_commit_msg.tmp         arbitrary-prefix .tmp variant
_commit_msg.txt
_tmp_commit_msg.txt
.commit_msg*
.git_commit_msg.tmp
*_commit_msg.tmp

# Local session evidence files emitted by ad-hoc verification runs
# (govulncheck, syft, soak harnesses). Useful operator breadcrumbs
# but never appropriate for the public tree.
_session*_*.log
_session*_*.json
_session*_*.spdx.json

# Runtime side effects of the `QSD` server when the operator runs
# a binary smoke-check (e.g. `QSD.exe --version`) directly from the
# repo root. Storage / governance / staking JSON, append-only NDJSON
# logs, and the auto-generated challenge HMAC are local node state,
# not source.
QSD_accounts.json
QSD_bridge_state.json
QSD_chain.ndjson
QSD_challenge_hmac.key
QSD_enrollment.json
QSD_governance.json
QSD_receipts.ndjson
QSD_staking.json

# Root-level state emitted by the local validator/bridge when launched from the
# workspace. Preserve these files for recovery and diagnostics, but never treat
# them as source or release inputs.
/QSD.db
/QSD.db-journal
/QSD.db-wal
/QSD.db-shm
/QSD-validator.state.lock
/QSD_bridge_state.json.last-good
/.QSD_bridge_state.json.last-good.*.tmp

# Legacy NVIDIA token file (pre-NGC-bundle era).
Nvidia Token

# NGC sidecar runtime envs (contain QSD_NGC_INGEST_SECRET).
**/ngc.env
**/ngc.local.env

# Generic .env files, except the committed *.env.example templates.
*.env
!*.env.example

# Treasury runtime configuration contains signer bearer tokens. Keystores and
# passphrase files must also remain outside source control.
**/QSD-treasury.json
**/treasury/*.json
**/treasury/*.passphrase
**/treasury/*.token

# TLS material used during early local testing. Production edge
# certs live on the VPS, not here.
QSD/api_server.crt
QSD/api_server.key

# Generic private-key / keystore extensions as a defensive net.
*.pem
*.p12
*.pfx
*.jks

# Wallets, signer credentials, SSH keys, and encrypted custody archives. Public
# wallet registries and funding plans use explicit names outside these patterns.
*.key
*.ppk
*.token
*.passphrase
*.passphrase.*
*.keystore
*.keystore.json
*.seed
*.aes256
**/wallet.json
**/wallet-*.json
**/signer.token
**/*.signed.json
**/*.unsigned.json
**/ecosystem-wallets.private*.json
**/credentials.json
**/.npmrc
**/.netrc
**/.ssh/
**/.aws/
id_rsa
id_rsa.*
id_ed25519
id_ed25519.*


# ------------------------------------------------------------
# 2) Internal development documents
#
# These are engineering breadcrumbs (what we did, what broke, what
# we fixed) that are useful locally but pollute a public repo.
# User-facing docs (README, CHANGELOG, LICENSE, MIGRATION_GUIDE,
# QUICK_START, and everything under QSD/docs/) are kept.
# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Fix memos of the form *_FIX.md — every entry in the tracked tree
# so far is a one-off post-mortem, not a user-facing doc.
*_FIX.md
**/*_FIX.md

# Status / planning / handover notes.
NEXT_STEPS.md
**/NEXT_STEPS.md
BUILD_STATUS.md
PROJECT_STATUS.md
STATUS.md
SUCCESS.md
READY_TO_START.md
RESTART_INSTRUCTIONS.md
PROJECT_STRUCTURE.md

# Local-only build guides. The canonical build docs live in
# QSD/README.md and QSD/docs/.
BUILD_WINDOWS.md
QUICK_BUILD.md

# Superseded architecture draft from the pre-Major-Update era where
# NVIDIA-lock was (incorrectly) framed as a consensus rule. The
# current, correct architecture lives in
# QSD/docs/docs/NVIDIA_LOCK_CONSENSUS_SCOPE.md and the README.
nvidia_locked_QSD_blockchain_architecture.md

# Token-system description that still uses stale "QSD" branding
# and whose main example is the external Greed Island game (a
# separate project — see §4 below).
QSD/TOKEN_SYSTEM.md

# Internal-only archive directory — 40+ fix/crash/phase-complete
# memos from the pre-Major-Update era. Kept locally as a project
# history, excluded from the public repo as "development documents".
QSD/docs/docs/archive/

# Other dev-breadcrumb docs that slipped into QSD/docs/docs/ itself:
# anything ending in *_COMPLETE.md / *_FIXES_SUMMARY.md, and the
# PHASE{N}_IMPLEMENTATION.md notes. User-facing docs (USER_GUIDE,
# QUICK_START, API_REFERENCE, MINING_PROTOCOL, NODE_ROLES,
# VALIDATOR_QUICKSTART, MINER_QUICKSTART, ROADMAP, etc.) stay.
**/*_COMPLETE.md
**/SECURITY_FIXES_SUMMARY.md
**/PHASE[0-9]*_IMPLEMENTATION.md


# ------------------------------------------------------------
# 3) Local operator scripts (per-workstation helpers)
#
# These are Windows PowerShell one-shots for spinning a local dev
# instance up/down. They are not part of the project's deploy
# pipeline (QSD/deploy/ and QSD/scripts/ are), and they hard-code
# paths that only make sense on one machine.
# ------------------------------------------------------------
OneClick-PlayAndTrain.ps1
start-QSD-local.ps1
stop-QSD-local.ps1
/QSD/restart.ps1
/QSD/setup.ps1


# ------------------------------------------------------------
# 4) Projects unrelated to the QSD ledger
#
# The QSD node exposes HTTP APIs that external apps (games, wallets,
# front-ends) can call from their own repos. Those integration
# scaffolds belong in those repos, not here.
# ------------------------------------------------------------
apps/game-integration/

# Separate private repositories and local historical copies. These directories
# may contain their own Git metadata, deployment credentials, or old secrets.
/external/
/Archived/
/QSD-source-office-copy-*/
/QSD-source-office-copy-*.zip


# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Agent-specific rules / tooling (not part of QSD)
# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Cursor agent rule files live at .cursor/rules/*.mdc and configure
# developer-side AI behaviour, not the ledger. Keep them local.
.cursor/


# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Scratch files from interactive agent sessions
# ------------------------------------------------------------
_tmp_*
**/_tmp_*


# ------------------------------------------------------------
# 5) Build artifacts
# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Go — Windows build output from local `go build`.
*.exe
*.exe~

# Go — Linux/macOS binaries emitted into source dirs. Scoped by
# path so we don't accidentally mask unrelated files of the same
# name elsewhere in the tree.
/QSD/QSD
/QSD/QSDminer
/QSD/QSDnode
/QSD/source/QSD
/QSD/source/QSD_local
/QSD/source/QSDminer
/QSD/source/QSDnode
/QSD/source/trustcheck

# Go — test binaries / coverage dumps.
*.test
coverage.out
*.cov
*.coverprofile

# Go — local tool/cache directories and editor/atomic-write leftovers
# produced under the QSD source tree during local verification.
QSD/source/.cache/
QSD/source/**/*.go.[0-9]*
/QSD/source/cmd/QSD-edge-control/rsrc_windows_amd64.syso

# Test runs write signed wallet transaction blobs here. They are generated
# evidence, not fixtures, and can contain public keys and signatures.
/QSD/source/tests/test_data/
/QSD/source/tests/test_e2e_data/
/QSD/source/tests/test_node1_data/
/QSD/source/tests/test_node2_data/
/QSD/source/tests/test_stress_data/

# CUDA kernel build artefacts produced by QSD/scripts/build_kernels.ps1
# (nvcc + gendef + dlltool). The only checked-in file is the .cu source;
# every derived product below is regenerated from it per-host.
QSD/source/pkg/mesh3d/kernels/mesh3d_kernels.dll
QSD/source/pkg/mesh3d/kernels/mesh3d_kernels.lib
QSD/source/pkg/mesh3d/kernels/mesh3d_kernels.exp
QSD/source/pkg/mesh3d/kernels/mesh3d_kernels.def
QSD/source/pkg/mesh3d/kernels/libmesh3d_kernels.dll.a
QSD/source/pkg/mesh3d/kernels/libmesh3d_kernels.so
QSD/source/mesh3d_kernels.dll
QSD/source/libmesh3d_kernels.so

# Rust (wasm_module/) — everything under Cargo's target/ is
# regeneratable and is where the local tree's large .pdb/.rlib
# accumulate.
**/target/


# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Runtime state
# ------------------------------------------------------------
*.log

# SQLite databases + WAL/journal sidecars produced by local runs.
# The timestamped *.sql dumps under QSD/databases/ are runtime
# artefacts as well (see QSD/databases/README.txt for context).
QSD/databases/*.db
QSD/databases/*.db-journal
QSD/databases/*.db-wal
QSD/databases/*.db-shm
QSD/databases/*_[0-9]*.sql
QSD/source/pkg/storage/*.db
QSD/source/pkg/storage/*.db-journal
QSD/source/pkg/storage/*.db-wal
QSD/source/pkg/storage/*.db-shm

# Per-transaction storage blobs written by the local node.
QSD/storage/tx_*.dat


# ------------------------------------------------------------
# 6) Language / IDE / OS caches
# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Python
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.venv/
venv/

# Node / JS
node_modules/
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*

# Editor / OS
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini


# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Ad-hoc deploy tarballs
# ------------------------------------------------------------
# remote_apply_paramiko.py packs the tree into a one-shot snapshot
# it uploads and deletes. Interrupted runs can leave one behind.
/QSD-snapshot-*.tar.gz

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Build artifacts (never check the binaries in)
# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Cross-compiled validator + reference miner. Both are
# regeneratable from source via `go build ./cmd/QSD` /
# `go build ./cmd/QSDminer` — checking them in would just
# bloat the repo and risk an out-of-date binary shadowing the
# source.
/QSD/source/QSD-linux-amd64
/QSD/source/QSD.linux-amd64
/QSD/source/QSDminer.exe
/QSD/source/QSD.exe
/QSD/source/QSDminer-console.exe
/QSD/source/QSDminer-linux-amd64
/QSD/source/QSDminer-console-linux-amd64

# Workspace-level cross-build output directory. Holds the
# Linux + Windows artifacts produced by `go build -o bin/...`
# during local deploys (e.g. before scp'ing to BLR1). Plus
# whatever per-operator deploy templates the bring-up dance
# produces (systemd drop-ins with HMAC keys, live-keyed
# TOML allowlists, throwaway awk scripts, etc.). Anything
# operationally interesting that should ship to other
# operators belongs in QSD/source/{cmd,docs,pkg,internal}
# instead — `/bin/` is a build cache, not a publishable
# location.
/bin/

# Local one-shot release-style staging directory.
/dist/

# A copied Electron runtime manifest can appear at the workspace root during
# unpacking. The real Hive manifests live under apps/QSD-hive/.
/package.json

# Cross-platform consumer release artifacts produced by
# QSD/scripts/build_release.ps1. Contains the per-platform
# QSDminer / QSDcli / QSD-attester binaries plus
# SHA256SUMS.txt and MANIFEST.json. Published manually to
# https://QSD.tech/releases/<tag>/ — checking the tarball
# into git would bloat the repo (~150 MiB per release) and
# create the same "stale binary shadows fresh source" risk
# the per-target rules above guard against.
/release/

# Website and desktop packaging output. Release artifacts are published through
# the release pipeline and must not be committed to source control.
/QSD/deploy/landing/downloads/
/apps/QSD-hive/QSD-hive-main/native/
/apps/QSD-hive/QSD-hive-main/release/build-*/
/apps/QSD-edge-agent/*
!/apps/QSD-edge-agent/README.md
!/apps/QSD-edge-agent/VERSION

# Stderr captures from local repro runs.
*.err

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Local one-shot deploy/operator scripts
# ------------------------------------------------------------
# .deploy_stagev.sh is the atomic-swap helper used during
# Phase 2c-v bring-up; it embeds a small operator workflow
# (backup → swap → restart → watchdog → rollback) that's
# specific to BLR1's filesystem layout. Kept out of the
# public repo because it would mislead operators of other
# QSD nodes who have a different /opt layout.
/.deploy_stagev.sh

# Throwaway PowerShell helpers used during local repro / debug.
# These accrete and are usually superseded within hours.
/.cache/

# session 87 (2026-05-12): local cross-compile output for ad-hoc deploys
_build/
# session 100 (2026-05-14): local cross-compile output for v0.4.x BLR1 deploys
/.deploy/
